{{Flavour|A shambling reanimated corpse. Trapped by evil spellweaving in a grotesque parody of life, this infected decaying body lurches about, seeking retribution on the living.}}
<!--monster-bot-end-->



==Useful Info==
'''Plague shamblers''' are putrid [[undead]] humanoids which seek only to spread the horrific [[rot]] that fills their flesh. Their powerful melee attacks inflict both [[sickness]] and [[retching]] in their victims, and upon death, their body spills out a rapidly expanding [[cloud]] of [[miasma]]. They can be found in [[the Crypt]].

==Tips & Tricks==
*Particularly slow characters ([[naga]]s in particular) may wish to [[blink]] away as soon as they defeat a plague shambler, or better yet, kill them at range. The miasma will spread faster than you can walk or slither away, and no one wants to rot any more than they absolutely have to.

==History==
Plague shamblers were added in [[0.13]], replacing [[rotting hulk]]s, and removed in [[0.15]].

